[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man shot in legs and ankles in west Belfast

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been shot in the legs and ankles in west Belfast, the Northern Ireland Ambulance Service has said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The attack happened on Bread Street, beside St Peter's Cathedral, shortly before 21:00 BST on Thursday.
The victim was brought to the Royal Victoria Hospital, where he is said to be in a stable condition.
